import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', bins=30, kde=True, color='blue')
    median_delay = data['delay'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_delay, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Delay: {median_delay:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Delay')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='distance', y='delay', data=data)
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between distance and delay?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.legend(title='Distance vs Delay', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    average_delay = data['delay'].mean()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=['Average Delay'], y=[average_delay], palette='viridis')
    ax.axhline(average_delay, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Delay: {average_delay:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average time of delay?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
